<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Defs>

  <!--
    Better Traders Guild - Bounded Defender Duty

    BTG_DefendStructure: Combat-engaged defensive posture that never assaults.
    Pawns with this duty, in priority order:
    1. Withdraw-and-tend when critically wounded, via JobGiver_BTGWithdrawAndTend.
       This sits ABOVE combat: a defender too badly hurt to fight without risking
       immediate death (bleeding heavily OR low overall health) breaks off, ducks
       out of enemy line of sight inside the structure, tends its worst wounds,
       then returns to the fight. The withdraw cell is constrained to the
       structure footprint, so it never flees into vacuum. No-op for mechs
       (Humanlike-gated). Distinct from node 3 below, which only tends when no
       target remains; this one fires even with hostiles in line of sight.
    2. Acquire and engage hostile targets, but only inside the settlement
       structure (target acquisition filtered by JobGiver_BTGDefendStructure).
       Combat outranks ordinary needs, so a defender never breaks off to eat (or
       to tend non-critical wounds) while a valid in-structure target remains.
    3. Self-tend wounds when not in combat. JobGiver_SelfTend tends in place (no
       pathing), so it needs no containment. No-op for mechs (Humanlike-gated).
    4. Eat when hungry, via JobGiver_BTGForageInStructure: carried rations first,
       then the best food source that lies inside the structure footprint. It
       never targets food outside the structure, so a player cannot bait a hungry
       defender out by dropping food past the walls. (Replaces vanilla
       JobGiver_GetFood, whose unbounded map search has no location filter.)
    5. Fall back to wandering near the focus point (radius 12) when idle.

    Containment summary - defenders never leave the structure because:
      * combat targets are filtered to the union of room rects, and
        JobGiver_AIDefendPoint (chaseTarget=false) holds firing positions within
        the duty radius of baseCenter rather than pursuing, and
      * foraging is restricted to food inside the same rect union, and
      * self-tend and idle wander are in-place / focus-local.

    No GetRest node: defenders hold their post rather than path off to sleep
    (another straying vector); tiredness is an accepted debuff.

    Used by: LordJob_BTGDefendStructure, assigned to the mapgen settlement
    defender group (human guards + gestator-spawned mechs). The forager is inert
    for mechs (no food need) but live for human guards.

    Design intent: model a "reverse siege" where defenders hold an entrenched,
    terrain-advantaged position and never path out of the structure to chase
    intruders or forage.
  -->

  <DutyDef>
    <defName>BTG_DefendStructure</defName>
    <thinkNode Class="ThinkNode_Priority">
      <subNodes>
        <!-- 1. Critically wounded: withdraw out of LoS (inside the structure) and
             tend before resuming the fight. Preempts combat by design. -->
        <li Class="BetterTradersGuild.AI.JobGiver_BTGWithdrawAndTend" />
        <!-- 2. Combat: engage in-structure targets before any ordinary need. -->
        <li Class="BetterTradersGuild.AI.JobGiver_BTGDefendStructure" />
        <!-- 3. Self-tend when not in combat (in place; no containment needed). -->
        <li Class="JobGiver_SelfTend" />
        <!-- 4. Eat, restricted to food inside the structure footprint. -->
        <li Class="BetterTradersGuild.AI.JobGiver_BTGForageInStructure">
          <minCategory>Hungry</minCategory>
        </li>
        <!-- 5. Idle: wander near the focus point. -->
        <li Class="JobGiver_WanderNearDutyLocation">
          <wanderRadius>12</wanderRadius>
        </li>
      </subNodes>
    </thinkNode>
  </DutyDef>

</Defs>
